# Kawaii UI Mandate

**Before writing or modifying ANY file in `frontend/**`:**

1. **Read `docs/kawaii-ui-bible.md` in full** — colors, typography, shapes, shadows, spacing, decorative elements.
2. **Read `docs/kawaii-interaction-system.md` in full** — motion, physics, gestures, animation constants.
3. **Confirm understanding** — both files are the law. Every component must satisfy BOTH simultaneously.

This applies to every UI agent, frontend developer, and animation specialist. Do this every time you touch frontend code. Not once. Every time.

## Quick Reference

- **Visual:** `.cursorrules` summarizes the aesthetic rules (or read the full bible).
- **Motion:** Interaction system defines scroll, button press, card swipe, pull-to-refresh, toggle, bottom sheet, tab switch, loading, celebration, toast — each with exact specs.
- **5 universal principles:** Spring physics, rubber-banding, velocity preservation, 1:1 direct manipulation, haptic punctuation.

## Team Scope

`frontend_developer`, `animation_specialist`, `ux_designer`, and `art_director` all build UI. They must all read and follow these docs.
